.TH "handle_domain_nmi" 9 "handle_domain_nmi" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
handle_domain_nmi \- Invoke the handler for a HW irq belonging to a domain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" handle_domain_nmi
.BI "(struct irq_domain *domain "  ","
.BI "unsigned int hwirq "  ","
.BI "struct pt_regs *regs "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "domain" 12
The domain where to perform the lookup
.IP "hwirq" 12
The HW irq number to convert to a logical one
.IP "regs" 12
Register file coming from the low-level handling code

This function must be called from an NMI context.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, or -EINVAL if conversion has failed
